The stability of the oxide electrodes, applied in processes of electrochemical oxidation of organic pollutants present in industrial wastewater, is very important. RuO2 plays significant role in stability of TixRu1-xO2/Ti electrodes because it undergoes serious corrosion in the oxygen evolution reaction. The stability of TixRu1-xO2/Ti electrodes can be attributed to reactions of RuO2 dissolution [20, 44]. The rate determining step includes the following reaction:2RuO2+H2O→RuO2–OH+H++e−\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
